<subSubSection id="12F1319A36FD8715333A4FD603DA7476" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BA2B92831F7AA8A22E1F12D6A54AA326" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="223EFC846D474218D06DA502E4EFDD99" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We did not find any original material for this name either in MAF (MAF-Pourret collection), and P (the general collection and the special 
<normalizedToken id="A9E1DA22E92C4CD77066F0B8D968CDB9" originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
collection named &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="CC183042798775392DB78C681E7757AA" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Chloris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chloris narbonensis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="narbonensis">
<emphasis id="C3546E987A723FF1B6741F40ADAAD224" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chloris narbonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;), where Pierre 
<normalizedToken id="7E2C3B582D46614F3BAC1E6D48F3A4D5" originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="6722FBF2471CC0C78975C8C7B6B97788" originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
(1754-1818) collections are mainly kept (
<bibRefCitation id="8606197137CB783B2BDA20E8AA0FF7F3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
), or in other relevant herbaria (BM, FI, MPU, and UPS; see 
<bibRefCitation id="3220F9D091FE5A6DDEC7B3D83A731FC9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
: 368). It seems, therefore, that the original material for this name is lost. This possibility is not surprising giving 
<normalizedToken id="46717EA4DE8B96AD06A5E718B28EEC4D" originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
dramatic escape from France to Spain in 1789 and his forced exile (
<bibRefCitation id="B9351BFF31C533B616BB16029A03721F" author="Galibert, L" journalOrPublisher="Italian Botanist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B11" refString="Galibert, L, 1856. Biographie de Pierre-Andre Pourret. Narbonne, Imprimerie D'Emmanuel Caillard." title="Biographie de Pierre-Andre Pourret. Narbonne, Imprimerie D'Emmanuel Caillard." year="1856">Galibert 1856</bibRefCitation>
), followed by several war events (
<bibRefCitation id="C68C802D9127E7517B6E899191F3C65E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
: 368). Because the original material of 
<taxonomicName id="8A65EA49ECE3C9F69B8480FB6A3B334C" genus="C." lsidName="C. villosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="9FA5C6BC624289AB186D2272AA78973F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lost, we have decided to choose a neotype represented by the specimen G00007761 housed at G-DC. This specimen has been previously selected by Cristofolini and Fumeaux (Cristofolini and Troia 2006) as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="5B37BE0DB7C2C81904DC904390233866" genus="C." lsidName="C. triflorus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis id="E6EE0725041CB9F06926DC7FCD16CA10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="72C8A1EEAFB65052067814DDD7AB48DA" originalValue="L’Hér">L'Her</normalizedToken>
. [1791]; an illegitimate name (a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="D3303BBD75DD9F1752017E4D5B25FFA0" genus="C." lsidName="C. triflorus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis id="347A1E6AFDCFD7FE508D7FFED5BC9323" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lam. [1786]) being conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="41841B238DC6B924BBDA1366CCA8C370" genus="C." lsidName="C. villosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="AAD2DEFE4964F8C7BDEB6276055C6C49" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pourr. (see 
<bibRefCitation id="6F7AA2BC96DA18F6557F974FDA8A09B6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" author="Polhill, RM" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B18" refString="Polhill, RM, 1978. Proposal to conserve and retypify the name Cytisus (Leguminosae). Taxon 27(5/6): 556-559. https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" title="Proposal to conserve and retypify the name Cytisus (Leguminosae). Taxon 27 (5 / 6): 556 - 559." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" year="1978">Polhill 1978</bibRefCitation>
; Cristofolini and Troia 2006). Importantly, as 
<taxonomicName id="90D259EF5A2ABD2B6EA9AC1E2C212F6B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus triflorus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis id="1F50A9225008FF648978FC1AC73B3CD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="10896399DFCAD9436A6EDD035F33D373" originalValue="L’Hér">L'Her</normalizedToken>
. has been accepted as the conserved type for the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="F096775B6E9EF8E04EB458FD76B2A70D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="29F3A89CF6C23DE43D868EBD265F0CEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf., nom. cons. (Appendix III of the ICN), it becomes automatically a homotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="0E59F05B1E4F0C9364B91DF2DF41FB91" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus villosus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="F642DEFD9E7ADE27752A0DF8862A8D76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pourr. - which is the accepted name of the generitype of this genus.
</paragraph>
